eats static final variables as constants. If a method isn't a compile-time constant and instead gets initialized at runtime, it complicates things. The initialization for a library in a native image might occur at build-time. Changing something may not impact the compiled branch if it’s constant-folded. But then, if the class is initialized at image build, maybe newGetBundleMethod is a non-null constant. And do HSQLDB classes initialize at runtime by default? It might be a mix of both, right?\\n\\n**Evaluating Java imports**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to handle imports in Java. It seems common that I should avoid using qualified names and just go for something straightforward, like `sun.misc.Unsafe`. But wait, I wonder if Checkstyle will flag that as an internal issue? I should probably check if there are any existing tests using this. It's crucial to ensure everything aligns for best practices while coding. Let's keep this in mind moving forward!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0eda5157bc4a7c690169f8e2ddd278819c8d83a2375e3eab8f\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-OMF6IA0uQBL8N1Obh6v9BkX2T5jpc2rJ8A-Mw-h0e0HZbCAi8TLW9F4vIYUQyK0tHheT7yjAaJVMTC7rshgoSak_9DuNQIDnrKSYaHcM0F0niOORlnoGQUkXmegaW5Q-1pfPSaKHUJnQ1lg4_M1nTfCMQnuUQvV65sRRscnbFSz08YGhglcIeR2Cdrbu9vJb0Y5gEcxpCr5f11bB7HDNNsyk6HOTt3WszgKnY5Gl4YvI1BmJpicLMy1pD4r9AoVCf0e7PRFy_mJrSNsIxmtrwJS-VLoboea2VcNIByfPJMbC3NTElHC3WLAN8TMNY1rRjQN7AjQLntWLHoCyI5DYbeYE-v9knTJg84sS3ZVJPURWbBpl__5EXDOFnUSP3JwNDmtRFVvLzuOekTY-r0kC-uLxQrZ_QDAARpZJMq4TYwYd7Cme-cCABLDNpdN1o03XeJztAPTvXVgtRR4usAkttTAfBGTU4h3_GSNl8X_TCkSBCWIPXLB41Atb1L1YEsRP6xvWePSpee5tF6kQgdKftN9h6S40QRUZnlvdntJxz6tDNIA3ELYLXBKK6_EJ3TXwf3Zw88Zj1bBiGFI75YFbCowjXAIWxOedBp5iG39X2xlydd06kEjcTJP-cO7q_9Q4vcR6TcF6xLNr1p2cQFBK0CKOPIkJ9UOwAGr3x2iOe-uhrt0HcjECXdjA_SDk8Q0Oi5DWs1Etz-JdpGZWxtlUnQdi3kJhkAPCRtlC6mgziZhBIliv0rCGRhxyDyOiZXd03sFpKjma1_5fATp8PNukIb0uJokpx2eGAyWfUO5vk_Th3KKFO5NdZ6z0ozmHlqWtWkqtpOTUGzsv8OV6PMHDVsD72d2ZU_LCm