icates things. The initialization for a library in a native image might occur at build-time. Changing something may not impact the compiled branch if it’s constant-folded. But then, if the class is initialized at image build, maybe newGetBundleMethod is a non-null constant. And do HSQLDB classes initialize at runtime by default? It might be a mix of both, right?\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating Java imports**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about how to handle imports in Java. It seems common that I should avoid using qualified names and just go for something straightforward, like `sun.misc.Unsafe`. But wait, I wonder if Checkstyle will flag that as an internal issue? I should probably check if there are any existing tests using this. It's crucial to ensure everything aligns for best practices while coding. Let's keep this in mind moving forward!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_LA2KjGVyBDtNXlO5UvdsUF4a|fc_0eda5157bc4a7c690169f8e3050690819c82bcd87a5de8dfaf\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/ResourceBundleHandlerTest.java\", \"limit\": 240}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 15474, \"output\": 2619, \"cacheRead\": 7168, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 25261, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777918684211, \"responseId\": \"resp_0eda5157bc4a7c690169f8e2dd15e8819c959c2af15bf61aa9\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_LA2KjGVyBDtNXlO5UvdsUF4a|fc_0eda5157bc4a7c690169f8e3050690819c82bcd87a5de8dfaf\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_hsqldb.hsqldb;\\n\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\\n\\nimport java.util.Locale;\\nimport java.util.ResourceBundle;\\n\\nimport org.hsqldb.resources.ResourceBundleHandler;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class ResourceBundleHandlerTest {\\n    private static final String SQL_STATE_MESSAGES = \\\"org.hsqldb.resources.sql-state-messages\\\";\\n    private static final String PROPERTIES_NAME_IS_NULL_OR_EMPTY = \\\"properties name is null or empty\\\";\\n\\n    @Test\\n    public void loadsBundleWithDefaultClassLoaderWhenNoClassLoaderIsSpecified() {\\n        ResourceBundle bundle = ResourceBundleHandler.getBundle(SQL_STATE_MESSAGES, Locale.ROOT, null);\\n\\n        assertBundleContainsExpectedMessage(bundle);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    public void loadsBundleThroughSuppliedApplicationClassLoader() {\\n        ResourceBundle bundle = ResourceBundleHandler.getBundle(\\n                SQL_STATE_MESSAGES,\\n                Locale.ROOT,\\n                ResourceBundleHandlerTest.class.getClassLoader());\\n\\n        assertBundleContainsExpectedMessage(bundle);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    public void fallsBackToDefaultClassLoaderWhenSuppliedClassLoaderCannotFindBundle() {\\n        ResourceBundle bundle = ResourceBundleHandler.getBundle(\\n                SQL_STATE_MESSAGES,\\n                Locale.ROOT,\\n                ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader());\\n\\n        assertBundleContainsExpectedMessage(bundle);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void assertBundleContainsExpectedMessage(ResourceBundle bundle) {\\n        assertNotNull(bundle);\\n        assertEquals(PROPERTIES_NAME_IS_NULL_OR_EMPTY, bundle.getString(\\\"0028\\\"));\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777918725607}]}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.hsqldb:hsqldb:2.4.1/add-new-